definition.value: The pyranose form of D-quinovose (6-deoxy-D-glucose) with beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A disaccharide derivative that is lactose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 of the galactopyranose ring has been converted into the corresponding hydrogen sulfate derivative.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylglucose derivative consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose and beta-D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
